eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.name
Class Rank

java.lang.Object
  eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.CdmBase
      eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.VersionableEntity
          eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.TermBase
              eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.DefinedTermBase
                  eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.common.OrderedTermBase<Rank>
                      eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.name.Rank
All Implemented Interfaces:
ICdmBase, ILoadableTerm, Serializable, Comparable<Rank>
public class Rank
extends OrderedTermBase<Rank>

The class representing the taxonomical ranks (like "Family", "Genus" or "Species") used for taxon names across all nomenclatural codes for bacteria (ICNB), viruses (ICVCN), plants and fungi (ICBN), cultivars (ICNCP) and animals (ICZN).

A standard (ordered) list of taxonomical rank instances will be automatically created as the project starts. But this class allows to extend this standard list by creating new instances of additional taxonomical ranks if needed.

This class corresponds to:

  • TaxonRankTerm according to the TDWG ontology
  • TaxonomicRankEnum according to the TCS
  • Rank according to the ABCD schema

Version:
1.0
Author:
m.doering
